div.p: Veelderhande cierlijcke compertementen profitelijck voor schilders goutsmeden beeldtsnijders ende ander constenaren, geinventeert duer IAQUES FLORIS. Tantwerpen bij Hans Liefrinck sijnse te coope op die Lombarde veste int gulden turckhooft. Anno. 1564. Harman Muller fecit.

Many decorative compartments, profitable for painters, goldsmiths, sculptors, and other artists. Invented by Jacques Floris of Antwerp. They are for sale with Hans Liefrinck on the Lombardenvest, under the sign of the Golden Turk's Head. Year 1564. Engraved by Harman Muller.
